  "faqs": [
    {
      "q": "Do you accept insurance?",
      "a": "Yes, we accept most major Saudi health insurance plans including Bupa Arabia, Tawuniya, MedGulf, Al Etihad, and Al Rajhi Takaful. Please bring your insurance card and Iqama on visit."
    },
    {
      "q": "How do I cancel or reschedule?",
      "a": "Send us a WhatsApp message at least 4 hours before your appointment. There is no cancellation fee with proper notice."
    },
    {
      "q": "Do you provide home services?",
      "a": "Yes, we offer home consultations and sample collection for an additional SAR 100 within Riyadh city limits."
    },
    {
      "q": "Can I get a prescription refill without a visit?",
      "a": "For ongoing prescriptions, our doctors can issue refills via WhatsApp after a brief consultation. Charge: SAR 50."
    },
    {
      "q": "Do you have parking?",
      "a": "Yes, free covered parking is available on-site for up to 20 vehicles."
    },
    {
      "q": "Do you treat non-Saudis / expats?",
      "a": "Absolutely. We welcome all residents and visitors. Please bring your Iqama or passport for registration."
    }
  ],
  "emergency_guidance": "For severe symptoms (chest pain, difficulty breathing, heavy bleeding, loss of consciousness, suspected stroke or heart attack), do NOT wait. Call 911 (Saudi unified emergency) or 997 (Red Crescent ambulance) immediately, or go to the nearest emergency room. We will notify our on-call doctor to follow up."
